The answers given are correct within the limits of the entity's knowledge. 'Unclear' is a legitimate answer, because powerful beings
of the outer planes are not necessarily omniscient. In cases where a one-word answer would be misleading or contrary to the deity's interests, the DM
should give a short phrase (five words or less) as an answer instead.
The spell, at best, provides information to aid character decisions. The entities contacted structure their answers to further their own purposes. If you lag, discuss
the answers, or go off to do anything else, the spell ends.",
